3Ô∏è‚É£ Phase C: Information / Application Architecture (TOGAF) + DDD Context Maps

TOGAF Deliverables
	‚Ä¢	Data Architecture Models
	‚Ä¢	Application Portfolio View
	‚Ä¢	Target Application Architecture
	‚Ä¢	Application Services Catalogue

DDD Tactics
	‚Ä¢	Create Context Maps:
	‚Ä¢	Upstream/downstream definition
	‚Ä¢	Shared Kernel, Customer/Supplier, ACLs, Anti-corruption layers, Conformist, ‚Ä¶
	‚Ä¢	Define aggregates, entities, and value objects inside each bounded context
	‚Ä¢	Define context APIs (commands, queries, events)

Outputs
	‚Ä¢	Application architecture organized around domain boundaries, not technologies
	‚Ä¢	Clear integration topology between bounded contexts
	‚Ä¢	Well-defined APIs and event flows

This is where many architects accidentally create distributed monoliths.
DDD keeps the architectural boundaries clean.

