üß≠ Cross-Cutting Practices: Glue Between TOGAF and DDD

1. Governance (TOGAF) + Decision Records (DDD/modern practice)

Use ADRs (Architecture Decision Records) to:
	‚Ä¢	Capture domain decisions
	‚Ä¢	Capture context boundaries
	‚Ä¢	Capture integration patterns
	‚Ä¢	Capture technology choices

TOGAF governance boards can review ADRs.

‚∏ª

2. Capability Mapping + Domain Boundaries
	‚Ä¢	Capabilities explain what the business does
	‚Ä¢	Bounded contexts explain how the business works internally

Mapping capabilities ‚Üí bounded contexts creates:
	‚Ä¢	Clean architecture
	‚Ä¢	Avoids spaghetti integration
	‚Ä¢	Enables modular development teams

‚∏ª

3. Portfolio Architecture + Subdomain Classification

TOGAF portfolio views should align with DDD:
	‚Ä¢	Core subdomains ‚Üí most investment
	‚Ä¢	Supporting subdomains ‚Üí selective investment
	‚Ä¢	Generic subdomains ‚Üí commodity, buy not build

‚∏ª

